## Vercel Web Analytics Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

### Changes Made:

#### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 using npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the resolved dependency tree

#### 2. Analytics Configuration
- **File Modified:** `src/app/layout.tsx`
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component to both layout sections (public routes and dashboard routes) before the closing `</body>` tag

### Implementation Details:

The implementation follows the official Vercel Analytics documentation for Next.js App Router:
- Fetched latest instructions from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Used the framework-specific approach for Next.js with App Router
- Placed the `<Analytics />` component in the root layout to track all pages
- Component is placed just before the closing body tag in both the public and dashboard layout sections

### Verification:

✅ **Build Status:** Successful
- Build completed without errors using `npm run build`
- All routes compiled successfully (22 pages generated)
- No TypeScript errors related to the Analytics integration

✅ **Linter:** No new errors introduced
- Ran `npm run lint` to verify code quality
- No linting errors related to the Analytics integration
- Pre-existing linting warnings in other files remain unchanged

### Next Steps:

To fully activate Vercel Web Analytics:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for your project
3. Visit your deployed application to verify the analytics script loads
4. Check browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*` endpoints

### Technical Notes:

- The Analytics component is lightweight and only loads when deployed on Vercel
- In development mode, it operates in a no-op mode to avoid tracking
- No additional configuration is required in `next.config.ts`
- The component is React Server Component compatible and works with the "use client" directive in the layout
